# Mobile & i18n rules

## Languages (exactly 3)

- Supported langs: `en`, `roman`, `ur` — defined in `frontend/src/locales/translations.js`.
- Every new UI string must be added to **all three** language blocks with the same nested key path.
- Run `node scripts/check-i18n.js` after editing translations.

## Translation usage

- Use `useTranslation()` and `t('key.path')` — no hardcoded English in shared components.
- Urdu text: prefer RTL-friendly layout; test nav drawer and forms in `ur` mode.

## Mobile performance

- Keep bundle lean: no extra language packs or heavy libraries without reason.
- Touch targets ≥ 44px; mobile nav drawer must work with one thumb (see `NavDrawer`, focus bar).
- Use `startVisibilityPoll` from `frontend/src/utils/visibilityPoll.js` for polling — pauses when tab hidden.
- Prefer CSS transforms over layout thrashing for animations; respect `prefers-reduced-motion` where present.

## Shop / gaming modes

- Gaming and shop transitions should feel snappy on mid-range phones (< 1.5s total).
- Test mode switch buttons on 375px viewport before merge.
